<DOC><DOCNO> AP880719-0308 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-19-88 1906EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Drugs     07-19 0401</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Earns-Drugs,0412</SECOND><HEAD>Drug Manufacturers Report Higher Second Quarter Earnings</HEAD><HEAD>By The Associated Press</HEAD><TEXT>   The nation's leading drug manufacturers reported double-digitincreases in both profits and worldwide sales of their health-careproducts for the second quarter.   Bristol-Myers Co., American Home Products Corp., Eli Lilly andamp; Co.and Upjohn Co. reported gains in both domestic and overseasoperations.   Bristol-Myers, based in New York, reported net income of $190.5million, or 66 cents a share, up 18 percent from $161.5 million, or56 cents a share a year ago. Revenue totaled $1.46 billion, up 11percent from $1.31 billion in the second quarter of 1987.   For the first half, Bristol-Myers reported net earnings of$401.13 million, or $1.39 a share, on revenue of $2.98 billion,compared with net income of $335.39 million, or $1.17 a share, onrevenue of $2.66 billion in the first six months of 1987.   American Home Products, also based in New York, reported netincome of $215.8 million, or $1.48 a share, up 10 percent from$195.9 million, or $1.33 a share in the year ago period. Revenuetotaled $1.37 billion, up 12 percent from $1.23 billion a year ago.   For the first six months, American Home reported net income of$452.9 million, or $3.10 a share on revenue of $2.78 billion. Inthe first half of 1987, net income totaled $412.3 million, or $2.78a share, on revenue of $2.52 billion.   Indianapolis-based Lilly reported second-quarter net income of$180.7 million, or $1.27, up 21 percent from $150.3 million, or$1.03 a share a year ago. Sales for the quarter totaled $1.01billion, up 10 percent from $925.9 million last year.   For the first six months, Lilly reported net income of $413.9million, or $2.89 a share, on sales of $2.09 billion. In theprevious year, the company reported earnings of $355.5 million, or$2.42 a share, on revenue of $1.89 billion.   At Kalamazoo, Mich.-based Upjohn, second quarter earnings rose12 percent to $87.8 million, or 47 cents a share, from $78.6million, or 42 cents a share a year ago. Revenue totaled $721.6million, up 10 percent from $655.5 million in the second quarter of1987.   Earnings for the first six months of the year reached $183.2million, or 98 cents a share, on sales of $1.38 billion, up from$159.5 million, or 85 cents a share, on sales of $1.26 billion inthe first half of 1987.</TEXT></DOC>